From f56267540e413e2f05efc70efff4e1a5919a2682 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Elias Ellison <elias.ellison@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 23:33:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [inductor] Layout-transform store sinking for channel-shuffle
 patterns (1.20x on affected ShuffleNet kernels)

Adds a post-grad FX pass that detects the channel-shuffle layout transform
pattern cat(dim=D) -> view -> permute(swap D,D+1) -> clone(contiguous) ->
view and rewrites it to unsqueeze+cat(dim=D+1)+view, eliminating the clone
kernel entirely: the cat on the unsqueezed dim produces the same memory
layout the permute+clone did, and the cat fuses with upstream producers.

Gated by config.layout_transform_store_sinking
(TORCHINDUCTOR_LAYOUT_TRANSFORM_STORE_SINKING, default on).

Measured (B200, 158-model corpus): 1.20x kernel geomean on the 14 affected
shufflenet_v2 channel-shuffle repros (flag ablation, control 1.0017);
structural kernel-count reduction (e.g. 3 kernels -> 1).

written with claude code
